A binary search tree (BST) is a binary tree where, for every node:
- all values in the left subtree are **less than** the node’s value
- all values in the right subtree are **greater than** the node’s value
- both subtrees are themselves BSTs

That property lets you search, insert, and delete efficiently by deciding at each node whether to go left or right.

```js
function TreeNode(val, left = null, right = null) {
  this.val = val;
  this.left = left;
  this.right = right;
}

function insertIntoBST(root, val) {
  if (root === null) {
    return new TreeNode(val);
  }

  if (val < root.val) {
    root.left = insertIntoBST(root.left, val);
  } else if (val > root.val) {
    root.right = insertIntoBST(root.right, val);
  }

  return root;
}
```

