781.answer:
A monotonic queue keeps its elements in sorted order as you push/pop, so the best candidate for each window is always at the front.

For a **sliding window maximum**, use a **decreasing deque** of indices:
- When adding a new element, remove indices from the back while their values are `<=` the new value.
- Push the new index.
- Remove the front index if it falls out of the current window.
- Once the first full window is formed, the front of the deque is the maximum for that window.

Why it works:
- The deque is always decreasing by value.
- Any smaller value behind a larger/newer one can never become a future maximum, so it is discarded.
- Each index is added and removed at most once, so the algorithm is **O(n)** time and **O(k)** space.

```js
function maxSlidingWindow(nums, k) {
  if (k <= 0 || nums.length === 0) return [];

  const deque = []; // stores indices, values are decreasing
  const result = [];

  for (let i = 0; i < nums.length; i++) {
    while (deque.length && deque[0] <= i - k) {
      deque.shift();
    }

    while (deque.length && nums[deque[deque.length - 1]] <= nums[i]) {
      deque.pop();
    }

    deque.push(i);

    if (i >= k - 1) {
      result.push(nums[deque[0]]);
    }
  }

  return result;
}
```

Example:

```js
console.log(maxSlidingWindow([1,3,-1,-3,5,3,6,7], 3));
// [3, 3, 5, 5, 6, 7]
```

If you want, I can also give the **minimum-in-window** version or a version with a custom deque implementation that avoids `shift()` cost.

784.answer:
An LRU cache keeps the **most recently used** items and evicts the **least recently used** item when capacity is full.

### Design
Use two structures together:
- **Hash map**: `key -> node` for O(1) lookup
- **Doubly linked list**: maintains usage order in O(1)
  - Head = most recently used
  - Tail = least recently used

### Operations
- **get(key)**
  - If key not in map, return `-1`
  - Otherwise move its node to the front and return its value
- **put(key, value)**
  - If key exists, update value and move node to the front
  - If key does not exist:
    - If cache is full, remove the tail node and delete it from the map
    - Insert new node at the front and add it to the map

### Why O(1)
- Hash map lookup/update/delete: O(1)
- Doubly linked list insert/remove/move: O(1)
- No traversal is needed

### Java implementation
```java
import java.util.HashMap;
import java.util.Map;

public class LRUCache {
    private static class Node {
        int key;
        int value;
        Node prev;
        Node next;

        Node(int key, int value) {
            this.key = key;
            this.value = value;
        }
    }

    private final int capacity;
    private final Map<Integer, Node> map;
    private final Node head;
    private final Node tail;

    public LRUCache(int capacity) {
        this.capacity = capacity;
        this.map = new HashMap<>();
        this.head = new Node(0, 0); // dummy head
        this.tail = new Node(0, 0); // dummy tail
        head.next = tail;
        tail.prev = head;
    }

    public int get(int key) {
        Node node = map.get(key);
        if (node == null) {
            return -1;
        }
        moveToFront(node);
        return node.value;
    }

    public void put(int key, int value) {
        Node node = map.get(key);

        if (node != null) {
            node.value = value;
            moveToFront(node);
            return;
        }

        if (map.size() == capacity) {
            Node lru = removeTail();
            map.remove(lru.key);
        }

        Node newNode = new Node(key, value);
        addToFront(newNode);
        map.put(key, newNode);
    }

    private void moveToFront(Node node) {
        removeNode(node);
        addToFront(node);
    }

    private void addToFront(Node node) {
        node.next = head.next;
        node.prev = head;
        head.next.prev = node;
        head.next = node;
    }

    private void removeNode(Node node) {
        node.prev.next = node.next;
        node.next.prev = node.prev;
    }

    private Node removeTail() {
        Node lru = tail.prev;
        removeNode(lru);
        return lru;
    }
}
```

### Example
```java
public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        LRUCache cache = new LRUCache(2);

        cache.put(1, 1);
        cache.put(2, 2);
        System.out.println(cache.get(1)); // 1

        cache.put(3, 3); // evicts key 2
        System.out.println(cache.get(2)); // -1

        cache.put(4, 4); // evicts key 1
        System.out.println(cache.get(1)); // -1
        System.out.println(cache.get(3)); // 3
        System.out.println(cache.get(4)); // 4
    }
}
```

