```js
function reverseGraphemes(input) {
  if (typeof Intl !== 'undefined' && Intl.Segmenter) {
    const segmenter = new Intl.Segmenter(undefined, { granularity: 'grapheme' });
    return Array.from(segmenter.segment(input), ({ segment }) => segment).reverse().join('');
  }

  return Array.from(input).reverse().join('');
}
```

`Intl.Segmenter` reverses by grapheme clusters, so combined emoji, accents, ZWJ sequences, and flags stay intact. The fallback uses code points, which is better than UTF-16 code units but not fully grapheme-safe.

