963.answer:
Use a per-cycle memoization cache keyed by the expensive function’s effective input so identical calls reuse the first result instead of recomputing it.

```ts
type Item = {
  id: string;
  raw: string;
  locale: string;
};

function expensiveFormat(raw: string, locale: string): string {
  // Simulate expensive work
  return raw
    .normalize('NFKC')
    .toLocaleUpperCase(locale)
    .split('')
    .reverse()
    .join('');
}

// Before: recomputes on every call, even for identical inputs
function renderBefore(items: Item[]) {
  return items.map((item) => ({
    id: item.id,
    label: expensiveFormat(item.raw, item.locale),
  }));
}

// After: memoized for one render cycle
function renderAfter(items: Item[]) {
  const cache = new Map<string, string>();

  const memoizedFormat = (raw: string, locale: string): string => {
    const key = `${locale}::${raw}`;
    const cached = cache.get(key);
    if (cached !== undefined) return cached;

    const result = expensiveFormat(raw, locale);
    cache.set(key, result);
    return result;
  };

  return items.map((item) => ({
    id: item.id,
    label: memoizedFormat(item.raw, item.locale),
  }));
}
```

If this is React, use `useMemo` to scope the cache to the render/input set:

```tsx
const rows = useMemo(() => {
  const cache = new Map<string, string>();

  const memoizedFormat = (raw: string, locale: string) => {
    const key = `${locale}::${raw}`;
    const hit = cache.get(key);
    if (hit !== undefined) return hit;

    const value = expensiveFormat(raw, locale);
    cache.set(key, value);
    return value;
  };

  return items.map((item) => ({
    ...item,
    formatted: memoizedFormat(item.raw, item.locale),
  }));
}, [items]);
```

## Bottleneck
The bottleneck is the repeated call to `expensiveFormat(raw, locale)` for duplicate `(raw, locale)` pairs within the same render cycle.

## Big-O
Let:
- `n` = number of items rendered
- `k` = cost of the expensive transformation
- `u` = number of unique input pairs

### Before
- Time: **O(n · k)**
- Space: **O(1)** extra

Every item pays the full transformation cost.

### After
- Time: **O(u · k + n)**
  - `u · k` for first-time computations
  - `n` for cache lookups
- Space: **O(u)**

If many items share the same inputs and `u << n`, this removes most redundant work.

## Notes
- Use a key derived only from inputs that affect the result.
- Keep the cache scoped to a render cycle unless cross-render reuse is safe.
- If inputs are object references, prefer a `WeakMap<object, Result>` when identity matters.

